About this item

  • 2.01" HD Screen Born to Fit The Wrist: Its 3D flexible surface design, extending seamlessly from the screen to the strap, presents a harmonious fusion of sleek curvature. Drawing inspiration from classic watches, this smartwatch encapsulates an elevated sense of style. The smartwatch is a perfect choice as a gift for family, friends, and loved ones.
  • Multiple Dials Transform Effortlessly: The fusion of design inspiration and technological aesthetics seamlessly combines practicality and fashion in the watch dial. Embracing classic styles, electronic trends, simplicity, and sportiness, it offers a variety of versatile options. The dial effortlessly complements any style, allowing you to switch between them effortlessly through the watch or app while also enabling you to personalize it with your favorite photos.
  • Answer/Make Calls Anytime Anywhere: By seamlessly connecting your android smart watch with your phone, these exquisite smart watches for women are compatible with Android 6.0 or iOS 9.0 and above. With the advanced bluetooth V5.3 technology, it ensures a flawless connection, providing an extended range of connectivity options. This allows you to effortlessly answer/reject/make/view missed calls, as well as view messages or receive notifications from popular social media platforms such as Facebook, WhatsApp, Instagram, Twitter and more.
  • Activity Tracker and Health Monitoring: These Activity trackers and smartwatches offer 120+ sports modes, including Running, Walking, Hiking, Badminton, Basketball, Boating, Climbing, Cycling, Fitness Training, Football. Swimming and Yoga are also included. These devices meticulously track exercise data with precision accuracy to help you plan and manage your personal exercise regimen effectively. Additionally, smartwatches for Android phones have advanced sensors for monitoring blood oxygen levels,blood pressure,and sleep tracking. With 24-hour heart rate monitoring and real-time updates through automatic uploading to the app,you can stay informed about your health constantly.
  • Genuinely waterproof IP68: In authentic trials, the AOLON Curve smart watch was fully submerged in water up to 1.5 meters for 30 minutes, yet no ingress of water occurred within the watch. This capability effortlessly caters to everyday activities such as handwashing, rain protection, immersion and perspiration during sports endeavors.
  • Enhanced Battery Life and Versatile Functions: It boasts a built-in high-capacity battery that can be fully charged in just 2.5-3 hours, providing up to 3-6 days (depending on personal usage), Bluetooth calls can be made for 4 - 5 hours. Additionally, the smartwatch and "Da Fit" app offer a wide range of practical tools including weather forecasts, stopwatch, timer, music control, find phone feature, intelligent alarm clock, camera control, women's health tracking features, sedentary reminders, etc.
  • AOLON Promise: We proudly stand firmly behind all of our products without reservation and we offer unparalleled 2 year quality support. Should you encounter any trouble with this smart watch, please do not hesitate to reach out to our exceptional customer support for assistance.

    How customer reviews and ratings work

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    Shmusie
    5.0 out of 5 stars very good watch for its price
    Reviewed in the United States on June 9, 2024
    Color: BlackVerified Purchase
    This smart watch is my introductory smart watch. I have never owned one so I don't have anything to compare it to but I will write based on my assumptions on what I presume a high end smartwatch should be.

    I actually think it is very accurate but I can't be sure since I have nothing to compare it to. However, the sleep, blood pressure, and other measures all seem to make a lot of sense and I have been testing it for about 2 weeks.

    It is certainly waterproof as I have taken multi showers with it and it has never been an issue.

    The battery life is good as well, as long as you don't get hundreds and hundreds of messages a day, and even if you do-it lasts a good 2-3 days on one charge so if you recharge it nightly (as manufacturer recommends) it should be no issue.

    The display is not AMOL and can't be set to always be on but the wrist flick does turn it on so it is not really an issue at all.

    It only stores 8 contacts which for a low priced watch seems to be just fine.

    All in all I am happy with this purchase and although at some point I may want to upgrade, I doubt it will anytime soon.
